Here's the full summary:

---

**What we built**
A personal discipline tracker called **TERMINATOR** — a mobile-friendly web app to track whether you do your daily routine blocks. Not a productivity optimizer, just a simple "did you sit down and do the thing?" tracker.

**The blocks tracked (Mon-Fri):**
- Programming x2 (06:00 and 21:00)
- Spanish x4 (15min blocks throughout the day)
- Reading x4 (15min blocks throughout the day)
- Biz x2 (07:30 and 18:00)
- Cold Calling (09:00-11:00) — simple yes/no, 50+ dials
- Gym / Cardio (16:00-18:00)

**Four logging states:** Done / Skipped / Work blocked / Did it later

**Three views in the app:**
- Today — chronological timeline, current block highlighted
- Week — full grid Mon-Fri with % per day
- Month — overall %, streak, per-category bars, heatmap

**Key design decisions:**
- Config-driven (block IDs never change, history stays intact)
- Data stored in localStorage + syncs to Google Sheet via Apps Script
- Hosted on GitHub Pages at alexkeller680.github.io/terminator

---

**Google Sheets sync — current architecture (as of session 2)**

The sync uses a pre-populated sheet (one row per block per weekday, 3 months forward from today). The app only ever updates the Status cell for the matching row — no row creation, no deletion during normal use.

Sheet structure (Log tab):
  Date | Block ID | Activity | Time | Status | Note

Three additional view tabs (created by running setupViews() once):
- Daily  — auto-filtered view of today's blocks (Time / Activity / Status / Note)
- Weekly — 14-block grid with Mon-Fri columns, status color-coded
- Monthly — one row per day logged, with Done / Skipped / Work / Later counts and % Done

Status color coding in all sheets:
  done = green, skip = red, work = yellow, later = blue

---

**AppsScript setup (do this when deploying fresh or after script changes):**

1. Open script.google.com -> your TERMINATOR project
2. Paste the full contents of the AppsScript file from this repo
3. Save -> Deploy -> New version (keep the same URL)
4. In the editor, run setupSheet() — populates Log with 3 months of weekday rows
5. Run setupViews() — creates/recreates the Daily, Weekly, Monthly sheets
6. Both functions are safe to re-run at any time (setupSheet preserves existing statuses)

---

**Known issues fixed in session 2:**
- Every button click was creating a new row (root cause: UTC timezone mismatch in date comparison + race condition from concurrent POSTs)
- Fixed with: spreadsheet timezone in toDateStr(), LockService in doPost(), debounce on frontend, pre-populated sheet approach
- Sheet was unreadable (all clicks logged as separate rows) — fixed with long format + per-block upsert -> then pre-populated sheet

**Remaining / future work:**
- Notes feature: Note column already exists in the sheet — user can type notes manually now. Wiring notes to the app (a text input per block) is a future task.
- The Monthly view only shows days that have at least one status logged (blank days don't appear). This is intentional.
- If 3 months runs out, re-run setupSheet() to regenerate forward.

---

**App is live at:** alexkeller680.github.io/terminator
